synonyms.bx: 最普通用词，着重指用某一方式载运，如使用交通工具、人力、畜力、管道等，没有明确的方向性，常可与介词 from/to 连用。

ex.enText: This train conveys both goods and passengers.

ex.chText: 卡车把煤从矿场运往各个城市和村镇。
ex.enText: Trucks convey coal from mines to various cities and towns.

ex.chText: 这条管道把天然气输送到我们的城市。
ex.enText: This pipeline conveys natural gas to our city.

synonyms.bx: 多指通过自然或人工形成的线路运送人、货物或输送能源等。

ex.chText: 早晨的邮件已经送走了。
ex.enText: The morning mail has already been delivered.

ex.chText: 他们把食物送到一座偏僻的村庄。
ex.enText: They delivered food to an isolated village.

synonyms.bx: 主要指投递信件、包裹、货物等，常可与介词 to 连用。

ex.chText: 这批谷物将于下周运往日本。

ex.enText: We are shipping you another machine today.

synonyms.bx: 指用船、飞机、卡车等运货。

ex.chText: 当地人用火车运送原木。
ex.enText: The local people transport logs by train.

ex.chText: 一些货运飞机被用来把食品运往伊拉克。

ex.chText: 卡车把农产品运往市场。

value.def: If you carry something, you take it with you, holding it so that it does not touch the ground.

example.ex: He was carrying a briefcase...
example.tran: 他提着公文包。

example.ex: He carried the plate through to the dining room...
example.tran: 他端着盘子来到餐厅。

example.ex: She carried her son to the car...
example.tran: 她把儿子抱上车。

example.ex: If your job involves a lot of paperwork, you're going to need something to carry it all in.
example.tran: 如果你的工作要求做很多文字工作,你就需要有东西来装所有文件。

value.def: If you carry something, you have it with you wherever you go.

example.ex: You have to carry a bleeper so that they can call you in at any time.
example.tran: 你要随身带着寻呼机,以便他们随时呼你。

value.def: If something carries a person or thing somewhere, it takes them there.

example.ex: Flowers are designed to attract insects which then carry the pollen from plant to plant...
example.tran: 花的作用在于吸引昆虫，然后昆虫再将花粉传到其他植株上。

example.ex: The delegation was carrying a message of thanks to President Mubarak...
example.tran: 代表团向穆巴拉克总统转达了谢意。

example.ex: The ship could carry seventy passengers.
example.tran: 那艘船可以载客70名。

value.def: If a person or animal is carrying a disease, they are infected with it and can pass it on to other people or animals.

example.ex: The official number of people carrying the AIDS virus is low...
example.tran: 艾滋病病毒携带者的官方数字并不高。

example.ex: Frogs eat pests which destroy crops and carry diseases.
example.tran: 青蛙吃破坏庄稼、传播疾病的害虫。

value.def: If an action or situation has a particular quality or consequence, you can say that it carries it.

example.ex: Check that any medication you're taking carries no risk for your developing baby...
example.tran: 仔细检查,确保你所服用的任何药物不会对胎儿造成危险。

example.ex: Individualism, and the breakdown of social harmony, had a constructive purpose. But they also carried a price.
example.tran: 个人主义以及社会和谐的崩溃具有一定的建设意义,然而这也是有代价的。

value.def: If a quality or advantage carries someone into a particular position or through a difficult situation, it helps them to achieve that position or deal with that situation.

example.ex: He had the ruthless streak necessary to carry him into the Cabinet...
example.tran: 他具有进入内阁所必需的冷酷性格。

example.ex: The warmth and strength of their relationship carried them through difficult times.
example.tran: 他们互相关心,关系牢固,这才熬过了艰难岁月。

value.tran: 使达到(目标);帮助…渡过(难关)

value.def: If you carry an idea or a method to a particular extent, you use or develop it to that extent.

example.ex: It's not such a new idea, but I carried it to extremes...
example.tran: 这虽然不是什么新想法，但是我将它发挥到了极致。

example.ex: We could carry that one step further by taking the same genes and putting them into another crop.
example.tran: 我们可以再进一步：取出相同的基因,并将它们植入另一植株。

value.def: If a newspaper or poster carries a picture or a piece of writing, it contains it or displays it.

example.ex: Several papers carry the photograph of Mr Anderson.
example.tran: 好几份报纸都刊登了安德森先生的照片。

value.def: In a debate, if a proposal or motion is carried, a majority of people vote in favour of it.

example.ex: A motion backing its economic policy was carried by 322 votes to 296.
example.tran: 一项支持其经济政策的动议以322票对296票通过。

value.def: If a crime carries a particular punishment, a person who is found guilty of that crime will receive that punishment.

example.ex: It was a crime of espionage and carried the death penalty.
example.tran: 这是间谍罪,应判死刑。

value.def: If a sound carries, it can be heard a long way away.

example.ex: Even in this stillness Leaphorn doubted if the sound would carry far.
example.tran: 就是在这样的寂静当中,利普霍恩也怀疑声音不会传很远。

value.def: If a candidate or party carries a state or area, they win the election in that state or area.

example.ex: George W. Bush carried the state with 56 percent of the vote.
example.tran: 乔治·W. 布什在该州以56%的得票率获胜。

value.tran: (候选人或党派)在(某州或某选区)获胜

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, usually use 英国英语通常用 take

value.def: If you carry yourself in a particular way, you walk and move in that way.

example.ex: They carried themselves with great pride and dignity.
example.tran: 他们举手投足间透着傲气和高贵。

value.def: If a woman is carrying a child, she is pregnant.

example.ex: There are many theories that claim to be able to predict whether you're carrying a boy or a girl.
example.tran: 有许多理论声称能够预测胎儿的性别。

value.def: If you get carried away or are carried away, you are so eager or excited about something that you do something hasty or foolish.

example.ex: I got completely carried away and almost cried.
example.tran: 我激动不已,几乎哭了出来。

value.tran: 急不可待;喜不自胜;忘乎所以

value.def: If a person or team carries all before them, they succeed very easily.

example.ex: In the formative years their alliance carried all before it.
example.tran: 在草创阶段,他们的联盟所向披靡。

value.boxu_tran: 不要混淆 carry 和 lift。carry 表示将某物从一处移至另一处, 其间不接触地面。lift 表示用手或机器将某物提离地面, 然后可以将之从此处移(carry)至另一处。
value.boxu_usage: Do not confuse carry and lift. When you carry something, you move it from one place to another without letting it touch the ground. When you lift something, you move it upwards using your hands or a machine. After you have lifted it, you may carry it to a different place.
